            "title": "BFF Bank: BNP Paribas crosses 3% regulatory threshold",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>(Alliance News) - BFF Bank Spa announced on Monday that it has received notification from BNP Paribas SA stating that the BNP Paribas group's consolidated holdings in BFF exceeded the 3% regulatory threshold as of the March 18 trading date.</p><p></p><!-- Article --><p>\nConsequently, BNP Paribas now holds, at a group level, 3.64% of the total shares outstanding and total voting rights.</p><p></p><p>\nThe threshold was crossed following several transactions executed on Borsa Italiana Spa's MTA market and over-the-counter by BNP Paribas's Securities Services division and its subsidiary, BNP Paribas Financial Markets.</p><p></p><p>\nBNP Paribas explained in a statement that \"the acquisition of these securities is in line with the normal course of our trading activities and implies neither an intention to implement a specific strategy nor a desire to exercise specific influence over the management of BFF Bank.\"</p><p></p><p>\nBFF shares are currently down approximately 46% at EUR1.73 per share.</p><p></p><p>\nBy Claudia Cavaliere, Alliance News reporter</p><p></p><p>\nComments and questions to redazione@alliancenews.com</p><p></p><p>\nCopyright 2026 Alliance News IS Italian Service Ltd. All rights reserved.</p></div>",
